Why It's Breaking:

  • .md.txt is not a recognized source file format by Sphinx.
  • Its likely that you originally had a .md file (for Markdown), but it was:
    • renamed or saved improperly, or
    • accidentally exported from a system (e.g., Windows or a browser) that appended .txt to a Markdown file.

Fix It Like This:

Rename the file:

If its meant to be a Markdown source file:

mv source/Voyagers_Vol_2_TOC.md.txt source/Voyagers_Vol_2_TOC.md

If it's meant to be .rst instead:

mv source/Voyagers_Vol_2_TOC.md.txt source/Voyagers_Vol_2_TOC.rst

Then update your index.rst:

Find the line in source/index.rst that looks like:

.. toctree::
   :maxdepth: 2

   Voyagers_Vol_2_TOC.md.txt

Change it to:

   Voyagers_Vol_2_TOC

No file extension needed Sphinx will auto-detect .rst or .md if configured properly.

Bonus: If Youre Using Markdown (.md) Files

Make sure conf.py has:

extensions = [
    'myst_parser',  # Enables Markdown (.md) parsing
]

And your requirements include:

myst-parser

    make clean
